'''CRT''' is the [[gene cluster]] responsible for the [[biosynthesis]] of [[carotenoid]]s. Those genes are found in eubacteria,<ref>Carotenoid biosynthetic pathway: molecular phylogenies and evolutionary behavior of crt genes in eubacteria. Phadwal K, Gene, 17 January 2005, volume 345, issue 1, pages 35-43, {{PMID|15716108}}</ref> in algae,<ref>Molecular phylogenies and evolution of crt genes in algae. Chen Q, Jiang JG and Wang F, Crit Rev Biotechnol., Apr-Jun 2007;, volume 27, issue 2, pages 77-91, {{PMID|17578704}}</ref> and are cryptic in ''[[Streptomyces griseus]]''.<ref>Activation and analysis of cryptic crt genes for carotenoid biosynthesis from Streptomyces griseus. Schumann G1, Nürnberger H, Sandmann G and Krügel H, Mol Gen Genet., 28 October 1996, volume 252, issue 6, pages 658-666, {{PMID|8917308}}</ref>

